commit.message: Clarifies the syntax for the run-dir option
Fixes the docs to correctly identify the use of the -i parameter when running from a remote directory.
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jawatson/voacapl into master
Corrected the output filename extension

Adds explicit dependancies to the makefile to force the mod files
to be compiled first when using the -jx make option.
Removes a couple of obsolete do with labels and uses end do.
Bumped version.
Bumped to v0.7.5.

Revised to delete the .da files correctly before running the area
calcs.
Adds a CLEAN to the makefile to pass the distcheck.
Removes the LP check and functionality from the dst converters.
Adds the module to the CLEANFILES to pass the make distcheck test.
Bumped version number.

Auto detects if we're looking at a short path (descending order) or
long path (ascending order) file.
Modified to include the getopt module
Revised file not found messages.
Adds a link to the source of the getopt stuff.

Modified to use getopt.  This changes the calls which must now use
the '--input' or '-i' prefixes.
Bumped the version to 0.7.3.
Includes the new man pages
Updated man pages to include the new utility functions.
Firts draft
Adds the new man pages to the distribution.
Adds some notes about the new absorption mode and run-dir parameters.

Fixes a bug caused by hard-coding the number of frequencies in the
pointer calculation.
Modifies the max path length to VOA_PATH_LEN + 13.
Removes a debug print statement.
Fixed so that it also works in the same directory.

Modified to write the csv/asc files in the same directory as the
source data files.

Modifed the syntax so that the single arg now directs to the data
directory containing the dst/idx files.  This makes it better at working
with user defined  run-dirs.
